        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-24 14:14:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> (8 comments)\n > \n > Olaf, all the clients currently access aaf components by\n > \"<component>.onap\".  Please explain how removing this won't break\n > RC1\n\nPlease take a look at: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/service/#dns\n\nYou do not need to add \".namespace\" (e.g. \".onap\") if the service is in the same namespace.\nCurrent implementation works only if namespace is \".onap\", which is simply wrong.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
